title: The Dennis Prager Radio Show SEP-18-2013 WED
description:
The Dennis Prager Radio Show SEP-18-2013 WED











Prager 20130918  3 Benghazi

Prager H3: Dennis talks to Fred Burton, 
 Vice President of Intelligence and Counterterrorism at Stratfor
 and Samuel Katz, 
 internationally recognized author and expert on Middle East security issues.
 Their new book is Under Fire: The Untold Story of the Attack in Benghazi

 Why is Joe Manchin, a Senator from the coal state of W. Virginia, still a Democrat? 
 That party hates his state.


Prager 20130918  2 Male/Female Hour: Love and Laugh

Prager H2: Dennis talks to Yakov Smirnoff, popular comedian,
 about the power of laughter to build and sustain relationships.


Prager 20130918  1 The Sounds of Silence

Prager H1: The musical event of the year in New York-a concert with big globs of silence
 Dennis talks to Hugh Hewitt,
 fellow talk show host and good friend,
 about the Republican strategy to defund ObamaCare.
 What are the chances that it will work?

 The new Miss America is a first generation immigrant. Her parents came from India.
